    "--- \n",
    "## Exercise 1: Loading the MNIST Data\n",
    "\n",
    "The MNIST data is stored in a special binary format. Our first task is to write a function that can parse these files.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Understanding the `.idx-ubyte` Format\n",
    "\n",
    "The files are stored in a simple binary format with a header containing \"magic numbers\" and metadata. All integers are **big-endian** (which is why we use `>` in the `unpack` function).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Labels File (`...-labels-idx1-ubyte`):**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Offset | Type | Value | Description |\n",
    "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
    "| 0000 | 32-bit int | `0x00000801` (2049) | Magic number |\n",
    "| 0004 | 32-bit int | 60000 (or 10000) | Number of labels |\n",
    "| 0008 | unsigned byte | ?? | First label |\n",
    "| 0009 | unsigned byte | ?? | Second label |\n",
    "| ... | | | |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Images File (`...-images-idx3-ubyte`):**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Offset | Type | Value | Description |\n",
    "| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
    "| 0000 | 32-bit int | `0x00000803` (2051) | Magic number |\n",
    "| 0004 | 32-bit int | 60000 (or 10000) | Number of images |\n",
    "| 0008 | 32-bit int | 28 | Number of rows |\n",
    "| 0012 | 32-bit int | 28 | Number of columns |\n",
    "| 0016 | unsigned byte | ?? | First pixel |\n",
    "| 0017 | unsigned byte | ?? | Second pixel |\n",
    "| ... | | | |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Your Task:**\n",
    "Complete the `load_mnist` function below to read these formats, extract the data, and return NumPy arrays. The images should be \"flattened\" from 28x28 to a 1x784 vector."
