    "--- \n",
    "## Exercise 2: Activation Function - Sigmoid\n",
    "\n",
    "Activation functions introduce non-linearity, allowing the network to learn complex patterns. The **Sigmoid** function squashes values to a range between 0 and 1.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Equation:**\n",
    "$$\\sigma(x) = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-x}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Derivative:** (We need this for backpropagation)\n",
    "$$\\sigma'(x) = \\sigma(x) (1 - \\sigma(x))$$\n",
    "(Note: The code implements this by passing the *output* of sigmoid, `x`, to the derivative function, so it's `x * (1 - x)`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "--- \n",
    "## Exercise 3: Activation Function - ReLU\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU)** is another popular activation function. It's simpler and often leads to faster training, as it doesn't suffer from the \"vanishing gradient\" problem as much as sigmoid.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Equation:**\n",
    "$$\\text{ReLU}(x) = \\max(0, x)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Derivative:**\n",
    "$$\\text{ReLU}'(x) = \\begin{cases} 1 & \\text{if } x > 0 \\\\ 0 & \\text{otherwise} \\end{cases}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "--- \n",
    "## Exercise 4: Activation Function - Softmax\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Softmax** function is perfect for the *output layer* of a multi-class classification problem. It takes a vector of raw scores (logits) and converts them into a probability distribution (all values are 0-1 and sum to 1).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Equation:**\n",
    "For a vector $x$, the $i$-th component of $Softmax(x)$ is:\n",
    "$$\\text{Softmax}(x_i) = \\frac{e^{x_i}}{\\sum_{j} e^{x_j}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Pro Tip (Numerical Stability):** Calculating $e^x$ for large $x$ can overflow. A common trick is to subtract the maximum value from $x$ before exponentiating.\n",
    "> $$\\frac{e^{x_i - \\max(x)}}{\\sum_{j} e^{x_j - \\max(x)}}$$\n",
    "> This is mathematically equivalent and prevents overflow.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Your Task:**\n",
    "Implement the `sigmoid`, `relu`, `softmax` functions and their derivatives in the cell below."
   ]
